[2] China: China National Health Commission 12 Mar 2020
Date: Fri 13 Mar 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202003/816e6f71236b4dca96378df5f6f4ae53.shtml


At 04:00 on [12 Mar 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 8 new confirmed cases, 7 new deaths (6 in Hubei and 1 in Shandong), and new suspected cases. 33 cases.

On the same day, 1318 new cases were cured and discharged, and 2483 people were removed from close contact with medical observation, and 237 severe cases were improved.

As of 24:00 on [12 Mar 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 13 526 confirmed cases (including 4020 severe cases), 64 111 cured cases, and 3176 death cases. A total of 80 813 confirmed cases have been reported, and there are currently 147 suspected cases. A total of 678 088 close contacts have been traced, and 12 161 close contacts who are still in medical observation.

5 newly confirmed cases in Hubei (5 in Wuhan), 1255 newly cured cases (1103 in Wuhan), 6 new deaths (6 in Wuhan), and 13 171 confirmed cases (12 358 in Wuhan). There were 3948 severe cases (3793 in Wuhan). A total of 51 553 cured patients were discharged (35 197 in Wuhan), a total of 3062 deaths (2436 in Wuhan), and a total of 67 786 confirmed cases (49 991 in Wuhan). 1 new suspected case (1 in Wuhan) and 49 suspected cases (44 in Wuhan).

At 04:00 on [12 Mar 2020], 3 newly diagnosed imported cases were reported) (2 in Shanghai and 1 in Beijing. As of 24:00 on [12 Mar 2020], a total of 88 overseas confirmed cases had been reported.

A total of 190 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 131 cases in Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (75 cases discharged, 3 deaths), 10 cases in Macao Special Administrative Region (10 cases discharged), 49 cases in Taiwan (20 cases discharged, 1 death ).

(Note: The cumulative number of confirmed cases has increased by 12 cases.)

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[According to the report above, a total of 80 813 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from China, representing an increase of 20 cases in the past 24 hours since yesterday's (12 Mar 2020) was prepared.

I think the final sentence alerts to the additional 12 newly confirmed cases since they prepared the report explaining the apparent discrepancies. It is now the 4th consecutive day that the number of newly reported cases in a 24 hour period was less than 50. While there are still suspected cases reported that presumably are waiting for laboratory confirmation, fingers are crossed this adequately represents China approaching interruption of the SARS-CoV-2 transmission in the country. In addition, 7 deaths were reported, 6 (85.7%) of them by Hubei province. Two new cases were reported from Hong Kong.

Again there were imported cases into China confirmed (2 in Shanghai and 1 in Beijing) bringing the total number of imported cases to 88. A challenge will be to prevent importations from starting new chains of transmission within China.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7084577,155. - Mod.MPP]

